WARP DRIVE PLACEMENT

If you place heavy items in the tech bay of the Vector, it may become imbalanced. To fix this you must flip the orientation of the warp drive to throw some mass downward instead of upward. This will rebalance the ship.

1. The default coordinates of the warp drive are (X=0.0, Y=81.5, Z=-7.0) To get these coordinates, use the move element tool and aim at the ceiling above the warp drive, then use the precision move keys. Use this position if the tech bay is empty.

2. To rebalance the ship when the tech bay has a lot of mass in it, move the warp drive to (X=0.0, Y=81.5, Z=-19.0) You can achieve these coordinates by aiming at the floor instead of the ceiling when placing the warp drive.

Press ESC to exit this text.

TECH BAY

The tech bay can house additional elements to adapt the Vector Voyager to specific roles.

1. You can place up to four L containers inside the tech bay. After placement of each container, link it to the secondary container hub - the top one in the engine room. To place the containers, aim at the floor, rotate container length perpendicular to ship length, and use the precision move keys to achieve the following coordinates.

(X=0.0, Y=114.0, Z=13.0)
(X=0.0, Y=98.0, Z=13.0)
(X=0.0, Y=82.0, Z=13.0)
(X=0.0, Y=66.0, Z=13.0)

2. You can place a Shield Generator L by aiming at the blue and black placement marker and using the precision move keys to shift it to the following coordinates.

(X=0.0, Y=88.0, Z=4.5)

3. You can place a DSAT by aiming at the yellow and black placement marker and using the precision move keys to shift it to the following coordinates.

(X=0.0, Y=78.0, Z=3.5)

4. You can also place an Anti-Gravity Generator S. I don't have placement coordinates for that or for the six pulsors - just wherever fits.

Press ESC to exit this text.
